# Docs & agent context

- Project map: `docs/README.md`. Domain math: `docs/explanation/math-model.md`.
- Active feature work lives in `docs/specs/active/<change>/`; archive when done.
- Decisions that must not be re-litigated: `docs/decisions/`.
- Keep `.cursor/rules` short; point at docs instead of copying long specs.
- Prefer tests + types as executable reference once code exists; docs own intent and tradeoffs.
- UI is not a golden layout — math correctness first.
- At triggers in `docs/README.md` (phase B2/C, ≥2 active specs, doc drift), self-evaluate full OpenSpec; report upgrade/wait with evidence. Do not wait for the human.
